.subsection Recalls

This section is pretty much automated, and will learn the intervals 
for each recall as they are first entered, so that usually, just a couple of keypresses will auto-generate the entire recall like the one 
shown below.

.image clinical/recalls/recalls_introduction.png

.item
.bold Recall list on Toolbar 
will always be visible no matter which section you are in as a constant reminder
.item
.bold Previous Recall list 
is accessed from the tabbed lists on the right hand side of the screen
.item
.bold Actioning menu 
is accessed by right mouse clicking over the recalls list and an Audit Trail 
is kept of any actions undertaken for a recall.
.item
.bold The Recalls Section 
to enter new recalls is selected from the recalls button on the main toolbar 
and recalls logged during current consultation will be shown underneath the recalls editing area.
.item
.bold Recalling Patients 
is a clerical task to be undertaken by perhaps your practice nurse or practice manager see 
.xref Recalling Patients
in the Admin section accessed from the sidebar toolbutton.

In the next section we will look at the information you need to enter to generate a recall.